[% META title = 'Daily Plan' %]
[% META description = 'How to use the Daily Plan: Start Day, Audit Todos, HelpDesk panel, morning notes, log' %]
[% META roles = 'admin developer' %]

<h1>Daily Plan</h1>
<p><em>Last updated: April 28, 2026</em></p>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>
The Daily Plan at <a href="/planning/daily">/planning/daily</a> is the starting point for each work session.
It gives you an at-a-glance view of what needs attention: open P1–P3 todos, open HelpDesk tickets,
and your morning priorities — all in one place.
The <strong>Start Day</strong> action runs an AI-assisted audit of blocking work and writes a morning summary into your daily log.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Table of Contents</h2>
<ol>
    <li><a href="#layout">Page Layout</a></li>
    <li><a href="#start-day">Start Day</a></li>
    <li><a href="#audit-todos">Audit Todos Panel</a></li>
    <li><a href="#helpdesk-panel">HelpDesk Panel</a></li>
    <li><a href="#morning-notes">Morning Notes</a></li>
    <li><a href="#log">Daily Log</a></li>
    <li><a href="#priorities">Priorities Panel</a></li>
</ol>

<hr>

<h2 id="layout">1. Page Layout</h2>
<p>The page has three always-visible collapsible panels and an action bar below the tab toolbar:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Audit Todos</strong> — P1/P2/P3 open todos</li>
    <li><strong>HelpDesk</strong> — open support tickets</li>
    <li><strong>Priorities</strong> — your current priority list</li>
</ul>
<p>
The action bar (below the tabs) contains the <strong>Start Day</strong> button and the <strong>View Log / Today's Log</strong> button.
These are always visible regardless of which panel is open.
</p>
<p>All three panels render even when empty, showing a friendly empty-state message so the layout stays consistent.</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="start-day">2. Start Day</h2>
<p>Click <strong>Start Day</strong> to trigger an AI-assisted audit of your work queue.</p>
<p>What happens:</p>
<ol>
    <li>The controller fetches all open/critical todos (P1–P3 across all linked projects).</li>
    <li>Todos are grouped by controller/subroutine and deduplicated.</li>
    <li>The HelpDesk open-ticket count is fetched from <code>/HelpDesk/admin/tickets_alert</code>.</li>
    <li>All of this is passed to the AI planning agent as a structured briefing prompt.</li>
    <li>The AI response is written into today's daily log as a <strong>Morning Summary</strong> entry.</li>
    <li>The log panel opens automatically so you can read the summary.</li>
</ol>
<p>
The morning summary gives you an overview of what is blocking, what HelpDesk tickets need attention,
and suggested priorities for the day — drawn from the actual state of your todo queue, not guesswork.
</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="audit-todos">3. Audit Todos Panel</h2>
<p>
The Audit Todos panel shows all <strong>open todos with priority P1, P2, or P3</strong> that have not been completed.
It is <em>not</em> filtered to today — it shows any open high-priority work regardless of date,
so nothing falls through the cracks.
</p>
<p>
CRITICAL and ERROR level application log entries also appear here at P1 priority.
WARN level entries appear at P3.
This means if the application logged an error overnight, it surfaces here at the start of day.
</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="helpdesk-panel">4. HelpDesk Panel</h2>
<p>
The HelpDesk panel shows open support tickets from all sites (CSC admin) or your site only (other site admins).
Click any ticket to go to the full ticket thread.
</p>
<p>If there are no open tickets, the panel shows a "No open tickets" message.</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="morning-notes">5. Morning Notes</h2>
<p>
The morning notes section shows a text area for your personal notes.
The auto-generated preamble (date, weather, system status — written by Start Day) is preserved separately;
when you save your notes, the preamble is prepended automatically.
This means you only need to type <em>your</em> notes — the system-generated context is never lost.
</p>

<hr>

<h2 id="log">6. Daily Log</h2>
<p>
The <strong>Today's Log / View Log</strong> button in the action bar toggles the daily log panel.
The button highlights when the log is open.
</p>
<p>Log entries are created and updated at <code>/planning/daily_log</code> and <code>/planning/update_log_entry</code>.</p>
<p>Each log entry records:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Date and user</li>
    <li>Morning summary (from Start Day)</li>
    <li>Personal notes</li>
    <li>Time entries linked to todos or free text</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2 id="priorities">7. Priorities Panel</h2>
<p>
The Priorities panel shows your current list of prioritised tasks for the day.
Items can be reordered, checked off, or linked to todos.
The Start Day button previously called "Good Morning" — that hardcoded link has been replaced
by the Start Day button which connects to the full planning workflow.
</p>
